Fifth Ave., east side, south from and including East 68th Street, showing at the S.E. corner of that point a vacant lot upon which stood the home of the late Charles T. Yerkes. Occupying the balance of that block front are the homes of Thomas Fortune Ryan (No. 858), and Alice G. Vanderbilt (No. 1 East 67th Street). The apartment house opposite the latter is No. 856 Fifth Ave. and stands upon the site of the former Judge Elbert H. Gary home. Returning to the foreground one sees partially at the left, the H. P. Whitney home, No. 1 East 68th Street

July 21, 1937.

P. L. Speer.
Neg #838

Fifth Ave., at and adjoining the N.E. corner of East 68th Street (right) as viewed in a southeastward direction and showing the homes of H. P. Whitney (No. 1 East 68th Street) and Louis T. Hoggin (No. 874 Fifth Ave.). The empty lot appearing on the right is at the S.E. corner of this point and upon same formerly stood the home of the late Chas. T. Yerkes. The side wall exposed by same is that of No. 868 Fifth Ave., a structure occupied by Thomas Fortune Ryan.

July 21, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
